# Aura Clock Tab - Project Overview

## Project Type
This is a **Chrome Extension (Manifest V3)** that replaces the new tab page with a customizable clock interface.

## Key Architecture Files
- [manifest.json](mdc:manifest.json) - Chrome extension manifest defining permissions and entry points
- [webpack.config.js](mdc:webpack.config.js) - Build configuration with TypeScript support
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and build scripts
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration

## Entry Points
- **New Tab**: [newtab.html](mdc:newtab.html) + [src/newtab.ts](mdc:src/newtab.ts) - Main clock interface
- **Background**: [src/background.ts](mdc:src/background.ts) - Service worker for extension logic
- **Popup**: [popup.html](mdc:popup.html) + [src/popup.ts](mdc:src/popup.ts) - Extension popup interface
- **Content**: [src/content.ts](mdc:src/content.ts) - Content script (if needed)

## Core Technologies
- **TypeScript** - Primary language (migrating from JavaScript)
- **Webpack** - Module bundler and build system
- **Chrome Extension APIs** - Storage, messaging, new tab override
- **Modern CSS** - Styling with CSS custom properties and animations

## Build System
- `npm run dev` - Development with hot reload
- `npm run build` - Production build to `dist/` directory
- `npm run lint` - ESLint + TypeScript checking
- `npm run format` - Prettier code formatting

## Development Principles
- **Modern practices**: Latest TypeScript, ES modules, async/await
- **Performance-first**: Minimal bundle size, efficient animations
- **SOLID principles**: Modular architecture with clear separation
- **Type safety**: Comprehensive TypeScript coverage

